 <H1>Highlights of System R Optimizer</H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Impact:
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Most widely usedcurrently; works well for < 10 joins.
</UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Cost estimation:  Approximate art at best.
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Statistics, maintained in system catalogs, used to estimate cost of operations and result sizes.
<LI>Considers combination of CPU and I/O costs.
</UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Plan Space:  Too large, must be pruned.
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Only the space of left-deep plans is considered.
<UL></P>

<P><LI>Left-deep plans allow output of each operator to be pipelined into the next operator without storing it in a temporary relation.
</UL><LI>Cartesian products avoided.</UL></UL></P>

